+# Parallel Synthesis Status
+
+## What works
+
+- **Parser linting**: config.mk parser correctly handles conditionals (takes default branch), wildcards (maps to filegroups), and warns about missing variables
+- **Synthesis**: 60/60 synth targets pass across 6 platforms (asap7, sky130hd, sky130hs, nangate45, gf180, ihp-sg13g2)
+- **Lint tests**: 55/55 pass (2 excluded: i2c-gpio-expander missing IO pads, aes-hybrid visibility)
+- **Lint floorplan**: all pass
+- **Parallel synthesis**: 6.8x speedup on swerv_wrapper (533s → 78s on 48 cores)
+
+## Architecture
+
+```
+Action 1: canonicalize (existing, ~15s)
+  → 1_1_yosys_canonicalize.rtlil
+
+Action 2a: do-yosys-keep (serial, ~24s)
+  reads canonicalized RTLIL
+  runs synth -run :fine + keep_hierarchy
+  → 1_1_yosys_keep.rtlil
+
+Action 2b: rtlil_kept_modules.py (fast, <1s)
+  parses RTLIL for keep_hierarchy attribute
+  → kept_modules.json
+
+Actions 3..3+N: do-yosys-partition (parallel, N=NUM_CPUS)
+  each reads keep RTLIL + JSON
+  picks modules where index % N == partition_id
+  blackboxes all other modules
+  reads keep RTLIL via SYNTH_CHECKPOINT (skips coarse synth)
+  runs synth -flatten -run coarse:fine + ABC
+  → partition_i.v
+
+Action 4: merge
+  cat partition_0.v ... partition_N.v → 1_2_yosys.v
+
+Action 5: synth_odb (BLOCKED - see below)
+  reads merged 1_2_yosys.v
+  → 1_synth.odb, 1_synth.sdc
+```
+
+## What's blocked
+
+### synth_odb after parallel merge
+
+The `do-1_synth` Makefile target uses the `do-step` macro which generates Make
+prerequisites for `1_2_yosys.v` and `1_2_yosys.sdc`. When Bazel runs
+`make do-yosys-sdc-copy do-1_synth`, Make tries to rebuild those files via its
+own dependency chain before running synth_odb.tcl.
+
+**Fix needed**: A `do-synth-odb-only` Make target that runs synth_odb.tcl
+without Make prerequisite checking. Or: restructure the flow so the SDC copy
+and synth_odb run as separate Bazel actions with explicit file dependencies.
+
+### Netlist differences
+
+The parallel netlist differs from serial because each partition independently
+runs the full synth.tcl pipeline (memory mocking, operator wrapping, etc.) on
+its assigned module. The serial flow runs these once on the whole design.
+Functionally equivalent but textually different.
+
+## Key files
+
+### ORFS (this repo)
+- `flow/scripts/synth_keep.tcl` — coarse synth + keep_hierarchy → RTLIL
+- `flow/scripts/rtlil_kept_modules.py` — extract kept module list from RTLIL
+- `flow/scripts/synth_partition.sh` — per-partition synthesis loop
+- `flow/scripts/synth.tcl` — SYNTH_CHECKPOINT support, SYNTH_BLACKBOXES before hierarchy
+- `flow/Makefile` — do-yosys-keep, do-yosys-kept-json, do-yosys-partition, do-yosys-sdc-copy
+- `bazel/orfs.bzl` — auto-enable parallel synth when SYNTH_HIERARCHICAL=1
+
+### bazel-orfs
+- `detect_cpus.bzl` — repo rule for NUM_CPUS
+- `openroad.bzl` — exports NUM_CPUS
+- `private/rules.bzl` — parallel partition actions in _yosys_impl
+- `private/flow.bzl` — parallel_synth kwarg handling
+
+## Pre-existing issues (not caused by our changes)
+- ihp-sg13g2/i2c-gpio-expander: missing IO pad cell definitions
+- gf180/aes-hybrid: platform PDN config visibility error
+- nangate45/tinyRocket: OOM on synthesis (large design)
+
+## Test designs with SYNTH_HIERARCHICAL=1 (temporary)
+- asap7/swerv_wrapper
+- asap7/cva6
+- asap7/ibex
+- asap7/jpeg
+- asap7/ethmac
